  "body": "The following can be looked at as potential candidates for spec code re-factoring. We can continue to add to this list in the coming weeks\r\n\r\n- [ ] Combine signing_hash functions. There are different signing hash functions after some forks/eips . See [signing_hash_155](https://github.com/ethereum/execution-specs/blob/a54fc2647b3eebcaf5307e831d6df8c59b77cfed/src/ethereum/spurious_dragon/spec.py#L766) and [signing_hash_2390](https://github.com/ethereum/execution-specs/blob/a54fc2647b3eebcaf5307e831d6df8c59b77cfed/src/ethereum/berlin/spec.py#L840)\r\n- [x] Transaction validation checks are scattered in the `spec`. Check if they can be brought together\r\n- [x] `spec.py` and `eth_types.py` aren't exactly the most descriptive file names.",
